> On Mon, Nov 08, 1999 at 01:37:59AM -0800, Android wrote:
> > Where should I go, or who should I ask in getting support
> > for the ATI Rage Fury video card? XF86Setup does not list
> > any compatible card in the Video Card section, and just
> > hangs if I try to select any other video card. The Rage Fury
> > is compatible with the XPert-128, but that card isn't listed, either.
> > ATI's website (www.atitech.com) only offers support for
> > Windows 9x and Windows NT - no Unix of any kind.
> 
>   If you don't want to use vesa framebuffer you can try SuSE X Server
>   (
http://www.suse.de/en/support/xsuse/
) for Rage 128 chip.
>   To have XF86Setup with its support you have to download SuSE
>   version from this page too. You can read about it there.
>   They're for SuSE 6.2 but should work with RedHats too.
> 
>   Besides, I tried it (Debian 2.1 - slink, glibc 2.0) and X Server
>   and also XF86 Setup hanged without saying anything. So I have to live
>   with framebuffer with annoying 60 Hz refresh :-(
 Their is ATI Rage 128 framebuffer driver in 2.3.26 now :) 
